{
  "texts": [
    "This ensures that the answers provided are up-to-date and rooted in real-world.",
    "The RAG framework, as described by [Gao et al., 2023b] and [Feng et al., 2024], operates by embedding both the user's query and chunks of external information into highdimensional vector spaces.",
    "These embeddings allow the system to compare and retrieve the most semantically relevant data from a vectorstore -a database optimized for highdimensional vectors.",
    "Once retrieved, this relevant data is used as additional input to the LLM, ensuring that the generated answer is informed by the latest and most pertinent information available.",
    "A key advantage of RAG is its ability to provide answers that go beyond the internal knowledge of the LLM."
  ]
}